      "problem": "Triangle ABC has A = (0, 0), B = (10, 8), and C = (7, 6). Find its area.",
      "answer": "2",
      "source_code": "import random\n\nCONCEPT_TYPE = \"geometry.trig_area\"\nCONCEPT_GROUP = \"geometry\"\n\n\ndef generate(seed):\n    rng = random.Random(seed)\n\n    while True:\n        x1 = rng.randint(2, 12)\n        y1 = rng.randint(1, 10)\n        x2 = rng.randint(1, 12)\n        y2 = rng.randint(2, 10)\n\n        twice_area = abs(x1 * y2 - x2 * y1)\n        if twice_area > 0 and twice_area % 2 == 0:\n            break\n\n    area = twice_area // 2\n\n    problem = (\n        f\"Triangle ABC has A = (0, 0), B = ({x1}, {y1}), \"\n        f\"and C = ({x2}, {y2}). Find its area.\"\n    )\n\n    return problem, str(area)"
